From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-13
Subject: [PATCH] sampler: extend --enable-nan-detection to catch +/-Inf

Cross-stack port from R9700 patch 034 (2026-05-11). File-level identical to
v0.5.11 mainline so applies cleanly on both stacks.

Sampler._preprocess_logits checks isnan(logits) but not isinf(logits).
softmax(+Inf) produces NaN (exp(+Inf)/sum(+Inf, finite) is NaN/NaN), then
torch.multinomial on NaN returns an invalid index, then torch.gather faults.
On ROCm this surfaces as HSAIL 0x1016; on Ampere CUDA it can manifest as
silent garbage tokens (the existing NaN check catches the downstream NaN
but you lose the upstream signal about whether the model produced Inf
or NaN to begin with).

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
index caa468b..d7a0df9 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
@@ -78,6 +78,19 @@ class Sampler(nn.Module):
             if crash_on_warnings():
                 raise ValueError("Detected errors during sampling! NaN in the logits.")
 
+        # Catch +/-Inf logits — softmax(+Inf) → NaN cascade then multinomial/
+        # gather fault (HSAIL 0x1016 on ROCm; can manifest as silent garbage
+        # tokens on Ampere). Same severity as NaN; --enable-nan-detection
+        # covers both. Ported from R9700 patch 034 (2026-05-11).
+        if self.use_nan_detection and torch.any(torch.isinf(logits)):
+            logger.warning("Detected errors during sampling! Inf in the logits.")
+            logits = torch.where(
+                torch.isinf(logits) & (logits > 0), torch.full_like(logits, 1e4),
+                torch.where(torch.isinf(logits), torch.full_like(logits, -1e4), logits),
+            )
+            if crash_on_warnings():
+                raise ValueError("Detected errors during sampling! Inf in the logits.")
+
         return logits
 
     def forward(
